AD_FIELD.NAME: Inventory Transaction
AD_FIELD.HELP: The ID identifies a unique record

AD_FIELD.NAME: Organization
AD_FIELD.HELP: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Movement Quantity
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The number of items being moved from one location to another.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Movement Quantity indicates the quantity of a product that has been moved.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Is Cost Calculated
AD_FIELD.HELP: Determines that the cost amount has been calculated

AD_FIELD.NAME: Is Cost Permanent
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Determines whether the cost is permanently adjusted or not.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Determines whether the cost is permanently adjusted or not.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Total Cost
AD_FIELD.HELP: Represents the total Cost of the Transaction including all the Cost Adjustments

AD_FIELD.NAME: Trx Original Cost
AD_FIELD.HELP: Total amount of the transaction based on product cost. Cost Adjustments are not included.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Movement Type
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The type of a certain item being moved from one location to another.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Movement Type indicates the type of movement (in, out, to production, etc)

AD_FIELD.NAME: Project Issue
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Issues to the project initiated by the "Issue to Project" process. You can issue Receipts, Time and Expenses, or Stock.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Issues to the project initiated by the "Issue to Project" process. You can issue Receipts, Time and Expenses, or Stock.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Currency
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An accepted medium of monetary exchange that may vary across countries.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the currency to be used when processing this document.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Transaction Process Date
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the date and time when the transaction was processed.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Movement Line
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An often automatically generated identifier for a movement line.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Movement Line indicates the inventory movement document line (if applicable) for this transaction

AD_FIELD.NAME: Physical Inventory Line
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A statement displaying one item in the physical inventory list.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Physical Inventory Line indicates the inventory document line (if applicable) for this transaction

AD_FIELD.NAME: Attribute Set Value
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An attribute associated with a product as part of an attribute set.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The values of the actual Product Attributes

AD_FIELD.NAME: Storage Bin
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A set of coordinates (x, y, z) which help locate an item in a warehouse.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Locator ID indicates where in a Warehouse a product is located.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Costing Status
AD_FIELD.HELP: Costing Calculation Status

AD_FIELD.NAME: Active
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_FIELD.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Product
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An item produced by a process.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Identifies an item which is either purchased or sold in this organization.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Movement Date
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The date that a certain item is moved from one location to another.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Movement Date indicates the date that a product moved in or out of inventory. This is the result of a shipment, receipt or inventory movement.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Production Line
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A statement displaying one item or action in the application.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Production Line indicates the production document line (if applicable) for this transaction

AD_FIELD.NAME: Client
AD_FIELD.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Costing Algorithm
AD_FIELD.HELP: Identifies a Costing Algorithm. Core distribution includes Average and Standard costing methods. Additional methods can be added using Extension Modules.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Goods Shipment/Receipt Line
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A statement displaying one item, charge, or movement in a shipment or receipt
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Shipment/Receipt indicates a unique line in a Shipment/Receipt document
